I like his top!!! And yes KooBits  seems very interactive and fun 👍🏻

What I ABSOLUTELY love about HBL is the opportunity to witness the growth of my children. Not just academically but physically but psychologically. When they were in preschool, I was always envious of their teachers who got to spend so many hours with my children teaching and watching them learn. Something I wished I could have experienced first-hand as their mom and fan. This circuit breaker and HBL sesh is giving me this exact opportunity now. I’m holding tight to this once in a lifetime experience. Never in the world would we have thought we could spend every hour of 2 months together with a primary-school-going-child!

My son has focus issue and always no follow instructions. However he can do well with Koobits and HBL.

What I like about HBL is being decide the type of curriculum for my child, based on her interest and subjects. It is a good time as a full time working mom to witness for myself my child’s growth and appreciate her learning experience. We connect better since we are now together 24/7. Despite all the challenges for me (juggling among work, HBL, housework), I truly treasure this opportunity to learn and grow with my child at home.
